jects were mobilized to regularly perform highly orchestrated civil air defense drills throughout the country. The war years in Japan are often portrayed as a landscape of privation and suppression under the censorship of the war machine. But alongside the horrors, pleasure, desire, wonder, creativity, and humor were all still abundantly present in a period before air raids went from being a fearful specter to a deadly reality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aAir defensesxSocial aspectszJapan. 0aMilitarizationzJapanxHistoryy20th century. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xSocial aspectszJapan. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aair defense, wartime, gas mask, Japan, visual culture, total war, consumer culture, pleasure, weapons, fashion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076650940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226816456423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226816456/original  a978-3-11-076650-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles